article.headline: San Francisco tops Loyola Marymount 82-59 for sixth straight victory
article.description: — Ndewedo Newbury had 16 points and San Francisco beat Loyola Marymount 82-59 on Saturday night to up its win streak to six.
article.linkText: San Francisco tops Loyola Marymount 82-59 for sixth straight victory
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- — Ndewedo Newbury had 16 points and San Francisco beat Loyola Marymount 82-59 on Saturday night to up its win streak to six. Newbury shot 6 for 10, including 3 for 5 from beyond the arc for the Dons (21-6, 10-2 West Coast Conference). Marcus Williams scored 14 points on 6-for-9 shooting. Robby Beasley III made three 3-pointers and scored 13. Alex Merkviladze had 24 points and 12 rebounds to pace the Lions (10-16, 3-9), who have lost six in a row. Will Johnston added 14 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
